              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004F.xml" title="preduploid" addr="jms-004F" type="local">preduploid</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is called a <html:em>duploid</html:em> when it satisfies the following properties:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>the preduploid <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004T.xml" title="univalent deductive system" addr="jms-004T" type="local">univalent</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>every <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004B.xml" title="positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">positive</fr:link> object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004X.xml" title="uniqueness of upshifts" addr="jms-004X" type="local">has an upshift</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>every <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004B.xml" title="positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">negative</fr:link> object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004Z.xml" title="uniqueness of downshifts" addr="jms-004Z" type="local">has a downshift</fr:link>.</html:li></html:ol>
